<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="3f81ced9-35a3-5750-a3ea-9f287421f3ae" activityNameId="2ff46715-879a-420e-9bd9-abfa11af5ad9" parentActivityId="f81f84cd-8997-41b3-998c-abfa1131f1ff" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">treatment of waste polyurethane, open dump, dry infiltration class (100mm)</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the waste being available at the location (gate) of the uncontrolled disposal. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the waste being disposed, in an uncontrolled manner and waste-specific emissions from open dump are released to air via gas and to water via  leachate.
</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'waste polyurethane' in an open dump. Recommended use of this dataset: uncontrolled disposal of the waste through dumping. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% PU . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 30.9 MJ/kg; net heating value 30.67 MJ/kg; H2O 2000; O 178700; H 84276; C 640700; S 203.07; N 60922; P na; B na; Cl 24369; Br 70.934; F 14.896; I na; Ag na; As 1.9253; Ba 188.99; Cd 82.301; Co 32.011; Cr 41.41; Cu 321.89; Hg 0.86045; Mn 80.984; Mo na; Ni 20.874; Pb 473.27; Sb 43.54; Se 2.128; Sn 26.555; V 291.99; Zn 566.54; Be 0.50667; Sc na; Sr 89.68; Ti 1013.3; Tl 0.40534; W na; Si na; Fe 3775.4; Ca na; Al 202.67; K na; Mg na; Na 1485. Share of carbon in initial waste that is biogenic 0%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 1%. 0.0002461 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="9a63625a-358b-4c1d-bf95-50ba038a759b">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents an open dump location of 'infiltration class 2 dry '. Location site with mean annual temperature (MAT) of 8 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 550 mm/year, and net infiltration of 100 mm/year. Temperature at site can result in permafrost conditions, which slows down water flow by a factor of (alpha t) 0.999. Total climate adjustments with alpha pt of 0.999. The leachate percolating through the open dump has an average residence time of 17.5 years. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Reference for climatic parameters: Doka, G., 2018, Inventory parameters for regionalised waste disposal mixes</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is an inventory for an open, uncontrolled waste dump for municipal solid waste. Ultimate average height is 7 meters. Operation phase duration is 15 years. The total raw gas mass produced from this waste is 0.00887 kg. The total CH4 mass in the raw gas is 0.006213 kg. Percentage of gas directly emitted is 100w%. A Methane Correction Factor (MCF) for air emissions of 0.7057 is employed. Leachate is not treated, but emitted untreated. Based on average waste composition and climate data the end of carbonate phase is estimated to be reached 7789 years after waste deposition. </text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2006-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
